            <h1>Bluethroat &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Luscinia svecica</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Muscicapidae'>Muscicapidae</a> (Chats, Old World Flycatchers (320))
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Luscinia'>Luscinia</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>svecica</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Luscinia_svecica.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Bluethroat &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Luscinia svecica</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Muscicapidae'>Muscicapidae</a> (Chats, Old World Flycatchers (320))
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Luscinia'>Luscinia</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>svecica</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Luscinia_svecica.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Bluethroat &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Luscinia svecica</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Muscicapidae'>Muscicapidae</a> (Chats, Old World Flycatchers (320))
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Luscinia'>Luscinia</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>svecica</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Luscinia_svecica.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;

    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Bluethroat &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Luscinia svecica</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Muscicapidae'>Muscicapidae</a> (Chats, Old World Flycatchers (320))
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Luscinia'>Luscinia</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>svecica</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

        <td>2013-04-18</td>
        <td> 06:01</td>
      
        <td>Germany</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=54.159&long=9.122&loc=Fieler+Moor%2C+Dithmarschen%2C+Schleswig-Holstein">Fieler Moor, Dithmarschen, Schleswig-Holstein</a>
        </td>
        <td>0</td>
        <td>song </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Sound was trapped in degenerated bogland with reeds, ditches and shrubs. Bird sang within two hours every quarter of an hour from the same shrub where the recorder was located. Pauses and many parts of song with wind noise omitted. Same bird as <a href='/130256'>XC130256</a>.</p>

<p>bird-seen:no</p>

<p>playback-used:no</p>

        <span class='common-name'><a href='/species/Luscinia-svecica'>Bluethroat</a></span> (<span class='scientific-name'>Luscinia svecica</span>)

        <td>
        <a href='/contributor/AZVRMQWBEK'>Volker Arnold</a>

        <td>Germany</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=54.172&long=9.127&loc=Ruesdorfer+Moor%2C+Heide%2C+Dithmarschen%2C+Schleswig-Holstein">Ruesdorfer Moor, Heide, Dithmarschen, Schleswig-Holstein</a>
        </td>
        <td>0</td>
        <td>alarm call </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>in pastures with ditches, shrubs and trees in a degenerated bog landscape. Bird imitates alarm calls of different other birds. Two parts with equal calls are omitted, the first one 30 sec and the second one 20 sec. Strongly filtered because of traffic noise.</p>

        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Luscinia_svecica.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

</script>

            <h1>Bluethroat &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Luscinia svecica</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Muscicapidae'>Muscicapidae</a> (Chats, Old World Flycatchers (320))
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Luscinia'>Luscinia</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>svecica</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Same bird and  same session as <a href='/133527'>XC133527</a>.  Recording distance  3-4m. In the beginning mimicing Oystercatcher when Oystercatcher passes at some distance.  [52.073, 4.452]</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Luscinia_svecica.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

function showSpeciesNr(value, data)
{
    jQuery('#species_nr').val(data.species_nr);
    jQuery('#quick-search-bar > form').submit();
    }

            <h1>Bluethroat &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Luscinia svecica</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Muscicapidae'>Muscicapidae</a> (Chats, Old World Flycatchers (320))
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Luscinia'>Luscinia</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>svecica</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

        <span class='common-name'><a href='/species/Luscinia-svecica'>Bluethroat</a></span> (<span class='scientific-name'>Luscinia svecica</span>)

        <a href='/contributor/LKSFUYYSUK'>Ulf Elman</a>

        <td>2017-06-07</td>

        <td>Sweden</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=65.103&long=14.447&loc=Stekenjokk%2C+Lappland">Stekenjokk, Lappland</a>
        </td>
        <td>800</td>
        <td>song </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Mimicking Wren  (Troglodytes troglodytes)  at <a onclick='xc.playFrom(374824, 4);'>00:04</a>. The Red-spotted bluethroat (Luscinia svecica svecica) in Scandinavia breeds exclusively in alpine birch forest and alpine salix shrubland, far from any Wren biotopes and the Wrens have ceased singing when the Bluethroat begins its autumn migration. It could therefore most likely not have learned to mimic the Wren as a nestling or during its early juvenile period. This may possibly seem to indicate that the Bluethroat's sensory learning phase is extended as compared to most Passerines, just as it is in the Marsh warbler (Acrocephalus palustris). See also <a href='/374670'>XC374670</a>.</p>

<p>bird-seen:yes</p>

        <td>Sweden</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=65.103&long=14.447&loc=Stekenjokk%2C+Lappland">Stekenjokk, Lappland</a>

        <td>800</td>
        <td>song </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Two Bluethroats, one nearby left and centre, the other more distant and to the right. The right one mimicks Icterine warbler (Hippolais icterina) at <a onclick='xc.playFrom(374670, 359);'>05:59</a>, <a onclick='xc.playFrom(374670, 106);'>01:46</a> and <a onclick='xc.playFrom(374670, 36);'>00:36</a>. Noise due to wind induced glitches <a onclick='xc.playFrom(374670, 12);'>00:12</a>-<a onclick='xc.playFrom(374670, 39);'>00:39</a>.</p>

<p>The Red-spotted bluethroat (Luscinia svecica svecica) in Scandinavia breeds exclusively in alpine birch forest and alpine salix shrubland, far from any Icterine warbler biotopes and the Icterine warblers have ceased singing when the Bluethroat begins its autumn migration. It could therefore most likely not have learned to mimic the Icterine warbler as a nestling or during its early juvenile period. This may possibly seem to indicate that the Bluethroat's sensory learning phase is extended as compared to most Passerines, just as it is in the Marsh warbler (Acrocephalus palustris), another excellent mimic. See also <a href='/374824'>XC374824</a></p>

<p>bird-seen:yes</p>

        2:21

        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=24.499&long=54.3446&loc=Lulu+Island%2C+Abu+Dhabi">Lulu Island, Abu Dhabi</a>
        </td>
        <td>0</td>
        <td>male, song </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Male bird giving spring song from low tree by reedbed. Flying round in response to playback and singing more strongly. Same bird as  <a href='/357596'>XC357596</a>. Two cuts here, taken only a minute or less apart. Some very distant traffic noise giving irritating background hum.</p>

<p>bird-seen:yes</p>

<p>playback-used:yes</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Luscinia_svecica.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};

    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Bluethroat &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Luscinia svecica</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Muscicapidae'>Muscicapidae</a> (Chats, Old World Flycatchers (320))
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Luscinia'>Luscinia</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>svecica</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Luscinia_svecica.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Bluethroat &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Luscinia svecica</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Muscicapidae'>Muscicapidae</a> (Chats, Old World Flycatchers (320))
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Luscinia'>Luscinia</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>svecica</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Luscinia_svecica.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;

    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Bluethroat &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Luscinia svecica</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Muscicapidae'>Muscicapidae</a> (Chats, Old World Flycatchers (320))
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Luscinia'>Luscinia</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>svecica</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Luscinia_svecica.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;

    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Bluethroat &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Luscinia svecica</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Muscicapidae'>Muscicapidae</a> (Chats, Old World Flycatchers (320))
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Luscinia'>Luscinia</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>svecica</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Luscinia_svecica.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};

    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Bluethroat &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Luscinia svecica</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Muscicapidae'>Muscicapidae</a> (Chats, Old World Flycatchers (320))
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Luscinia'>Luscinia</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>svecica</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

        <td>800</td>
        <td>male, song </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>This recording and six others (bhk1-bhk7) were made while following the birds with a video camera, which explains some occasional noise. However the constant background sound is not noise but the stream StorÃ¥n. Recorded with a Telinga Pro 5 parabole and a stereo DAT microphone, no filters. Regrettably the time for each recording was not noted so 15.00 is not correct, but the birds were singing most of the day. I do not know how many bluethroats are represented in the seven recordings but there is only one per recording.</p>

<p>A collage of video clips from the same occasion can be found at http://captainmnemo.se/audiovisual/bhk6.</p>

        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Luscinia_svecica.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

</script>

            <h1>Bluethroat &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Luscinia svecica</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Muscicapidae'>Muscicapidae</a> (Chats, Old World Flycatchers (320))
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Luscinia'>Luscinia</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>svecica</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Luscinia_svecica.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;

    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Bluethroat &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Luscinia svecica</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Muscicapidae'>Muscicapidae</a> (Chats, Old World Flycatchers (320))
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Luscinia'>Luscinia</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>svecica</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Luscinia_svecica.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};

    xcmap = xc.initMap();

            <h1>Bluethroat &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Luscinia svecica</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Linnaeus, 1758)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Muscicapidae'>Muscicapidae</a> (Chats, Old World Flycatchers (320))
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Luscinia'>Luscinia</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>svecica</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Luscinia_svecica.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});
